== Other divisions of the site (historical) ==

* [[Plutonium Finishing Plant]] (PFP) - made plutonium metal for use in weapons<ref name="LiniRogers">

 {{cite web |title = Plutonium Finishing Plant Plutonium- Uranium Oxide |url = http://www.osti.gov/bridge/servlets/purl/808358-Jnqfum/native/808358.pdf |format = PDF|author = Lini, D.C. and L. H. Rodgers / SAIC / FH | accessdate = October 1, 2009 |publisher = [[US Department of Energy|US DOE]] | date = March 2002 }}

</ref>
* B Plant, S Plant, T Plant - processing, separation, and extraction of various chemicals and isotopes<ref name="atli"/><ref name="Gerber2001"/>
* Health Instruments Section - an attempt to keep workers and the environment safe<ref  name="Gerber2001">

 {{ cite web | url = http://www.osti.gov/energycitations/servlets/purl/805998-ZttWY8/native/805998.pdf | title = History of Hanford Site Defense Production (Brief)  | author = Gerber, M.S. | date = 2001 Feb | accessdate = October 1, 2009 |format = PDF |publisher = [[Fluor Hanford]] / [[US DOE]] }}

</ref>
* REDOX Plant / C Plant - recovered wasted uranium from WWII processes<ref name="Gerber2001"/>
* Experimental Animal Farm and Aquatic Biology Laboratory<ref name="Gerber2001"/>
* Technical Center - radiochemistry, physics, metallurgy, biophysics, radioactive sewer, neutralization, metal fab, fuels manufacturing<ref name="Gerber2001"/>
* Tank Farms - storage of liquid nuclear waste<ref name="Gerber2001"/>
* Metal Recovery Plant / U Plant - recover uranium from tank farms<ref name="Gerber2001"/>
* Uranium Trioxide Plant (aka Uranium Oxide Plant aka UO3 Plant) - took output from other plants (i.e. liquid [[uranyl nitrate hexahydrate]] from U plant and PUREX plant), made [[uranium trioxide]] powder<ref name="atli">

{{cite web  | url = http://www.atlintl.com/Services-222-SHanfordSite.html  | title = 222-S  Hanford Site | accessdate = October 1, 2009   | publisher = Advanced  Technologies and Laboratories Intl }}

</ref><ref name="Gerber2001"/><ref name="freer_conway_2002">

{{cite web | url = http://www.hanford.gov/doe/history/docs/rl-97-1047/c2_s4.pdf |title = History of the Plutonium Production Facilities at the Hanford Site Historic District, 1943-1990. Section 4 - Chemical Separations.| date = June 2002 | publisher  = [[US DOE]] | author = Freer, Brian and Charles Conway |format = PDF}}

</ref><ref name="brevick1997">

{{cite web | url = http://www.osti.gov/bridge/servlets/purl/311008-27Uxdp/webviewable/| title = Supporting Document for the Historical Tank Content Estimate for SY-Tank Farm| year = 1997 | author = Brevick, Stroup, Funk, ''et al.'' | publisher = [[US DOE]] | accessdate = October 5, 2009 }} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}}

</ref><ref name="johnson1994">

{{cite web 
|url = http://www.osti.gov/bridge/product.biblio.jsp?osti_id=10191138|title = Historical records of radioactive contamination in biota at the 200 Areas of the Hanford Site |author = Johnson, ''et al.'' | year = 1994 | accessdate = October 5, 2009|publisher = [[US DOE]] }}

</ref><ref name="carbaugh2003">

{{cite web | url = http://www.pnl.gov/main/publications/external/technical_reports/PNNL-15614.pdf | title = Methods and Models of the Hanford Internal Dosimetry Program, PNNL-MA-860| author = Carbaugh E.H., Bihl, D.E., and MacLellan,J.A. | date = January 1, 2003 | accessdate = October 5, 2009 |format = PDF}}

</ref><ref name="hanford_1">

{{cite web 
